Dyeing traditions in Estonia, dye chemistry basics, practical dyeing with natural and synthetic dyes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of traditional dyes, dyeing techniques used in Estonia and dye chemistry basics. To teach students dyeing of woolen yarn with natural and synthetic dyes.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: - has an overview of traditional dye techniques and dyes used in Estonian traditional clothing; - knows most important local dye plants; - has a basic knowledge of dye chemistry; - can prepare woolen yarn for dyeing with natural and synthetic dyes; - can prepare dye baths with natural and synthetic dyes, can dye woolen yarn and knows how to finish dyed yarn; - can compose and test dye recipes and make dye samples.
